task.summary: Because with this the entire plugin was rewritten there may be some bugs I have overlooked please report them to me - Rewrote the entire plugin - Now uses the [CommandAPI](https://commandapi.jorel.dev) - Made the src available - Added a permission system - Added a reply command - Added highlighting for chat messages with your name - Added a fly speed command - Some other small changes and fixes
Changed available version in issue template

Fixed some small errors Changed some messages slightly Made players with the tgc-system.team permission able to use colorcodes in chat Changed left forEach to for loops for a minimal better performance

Fixed some small errors Fixed MaintenanceCommand Fixed AutoSave and made it use BukkitRunnable Changed some messages slightly Made players with the tgc-system.team permission able to use colorcodes in chat Changed left forEach to for loops for a minimal better performance Removed default maintenance-icon Differentiated plugin version and config version Simplified sendToTeam methode Added modrinth link while it is not even on there (at the moment)

Fixed error in onDisable if you don't have AutoSave enabled Fixed version check returning true when the version isn't set Fixed the config in the ReadMe Renamed the version in the config to ConfigVersion because it is a different version than the pluings version Removed default maintenance-icon file Added hidden motd mode Added easy harvest Added [CommandAPI](https://github.com/JorelAli/CommandAPI) dependency to ReadMe
Added an extra layer of security for loading the resource pack with force Added a update checker (will return false until release is uploaded to modrinth) Tweaked some other things slightly
Fixed the config version in the ReadMe examples
Changed versions in bug report template

Added a simple TeamChat Added a walk speed command Added a speed command Added the say command because chat reporting also applies there Updated CommandAPI to version 9.0.1 -> RebootCommands max minutes can now be as high as the int limit Reworked the StatusHandler so it no longer relies on minecrafts teams
